.SH NAME
.B ddi_get_time
\- get the current time in seconds since the Epoch.
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #define _SUN_SOURCE
.br
.B #include <sys/stream.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/dki.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/ddi.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/sunddi.h>
.HP
.B time_t ddi_get_time(void);
.\"
.\"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
None.
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
returns the current value of the system clock in seconds from the epoch.
.BR ddi_get_time ()
is a SUNDDI specific function intended to replace
.BR drv_getparm (9).
Both are a system independent way for a
.I STREAMS
driver or module to obtain the value of the system clock.
.\"
.\"
.SH RETURN
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
returns the current value of the system clock in seconds from the epoch.
.\"
.\"
.SH ERRORS
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
always succeeds.
.\"
.\"
.SH CONTEXT
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
can be called from any context, including user context, module procedures,
callouts, callbacks, soft interrupts (tasklets and bottom halves), and interrupt service routines.
.\"
.\"
.SH MP-STREAMS
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
is MP-safe.
.\"
.\"
.SH NOTICES
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
is a
.IR Solaris \(rg-specific
function:
.B _SUN_SOURCE
must be defined before including DDI/DKI include files to expose this
symbol.
.B Linux Fast-STREAMS
must also have been compiled with
.B CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_SUN
or
.B CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_SUN_MODULE
set.
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
returns the seconds component of the return from a call to
.BR do_gettimeofday (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR drv_getparm (9),
.BR do_gettimeofday (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
has no known bugs.
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
.BR ddi_get_time ()
is provided for source compatibility with
.IR Solaris \(rg
for the purpose of porting
.IR Solaris \(rg
drivers to
.BR Linux .
.IP \(em
Binary compatibility is not guaranteed.
.PP
See
.BR suncompat (9)
for additional compatibility information.
.\"
.\"
